pageContext.claim: “Just got back from Asia. I brought back $300 billion worth of deals.”
pageContext.analysis: This is not accurate. Many of the arrangements are non-binding memorandums rather than legal contracts, valued at $250 billion. Still, it remains to be seen if the initial contracts will come to fruition. And despite the claims of success, the trade deficit with China has grown 7 percent from January to October, according to a December report from the Commerce Department.
